Company: Sterling and Wilson Renewable Energy
Position: Procurement Buyer
Location: Chembur, Mumbai
Experience: 8 – 10 Years
Salary Budget: ₹15 LPA – ₹18 LPA
Industry: Transmission &amp; Distribution / Metro / Substation Projects

Job Summary

We are looking for an experienced Procurement Buyer with strong experience in electrical procurement for transmission, distribution, metro, or substation projects. The candidate will be responsible for vendor management, techno-commercial evaluation, procurement planning, and contract management to ensure timely project execution.

Key Responsibilities

Floating enquiries to vendors and obtaining techno-commercial offers within timelines

Evaluation and comparison of commercial and technical proposals

Conduct cost analysis to determine optimal procurement cost

Coordinate post-technical evaluation commercial negotiations with vendors

Contract finalization ensuring minimal commercial and contractual risk

Maintain documentation required for technical evaluation and procurement approvals

Contract management and supplier relationship management

Ensure timely material delivery aligned with project schedules

Coordinate logistics with project execution teams

Maintain Procurement Tracker and MIS reports

Work with SAP MM module for procurement processes

Manage import/export procurement and freight forwarding

New vendor identification and development

Conduct periodic vendor performance evaluation (quality, delivery, cost)

Coordinate with finance for payment follow-ups

Support project teams for execution and procurement coordination

Qualification

Graduate Electrical Engineer from a recognized engineering institute

Post Graduate Diploma in Material Management (preferred)

8 – 10 years experience in Transmission &amp; Distribution / EPC / Metro / Substation projects

Required Skills

Strong knowledge of electrical items used in Metro / Substation projects

Experience in vendor negotiation and procurement strategy

Ability to develop cost basis for engineering products and services

Experience with SAP MM module

Exposure to import/export procurement and freight forwarding

Strong Excel, reporting, and documentation skills

Excellent communication and coordination abilities

Apply Now – Candidate Details Required

Interested candidates are requested to share the below details along with their updated CV.

Full Name

Contact Number

Email ID

Current Location

Are you willing to relocate to Mumbai (Chembur)?

Total Work Experience

Relevant Procurement Experience in Transmission / Distribution / Substation / Metro Projects (Years)

Current Company Name

Current Designation

Current CTC

Expected CTC

Notice Period

Highest Qualification

Do you have Electrical Engineering qualification? (Yes/No)

Do you have PG Diploma in Material Management? (Yes/No)

Experience working with SAP MM Module (Years)

Experience in Import / Export procurement &amp; Freight Forwarding

Experience in Vendor Development &amp; Vendor Evaluation

Experience handling Techno-commercial negotiations (Yes/No)

Experience in Metro / Substation project procurement (Yes/No)

Marital Status

Current Employment Status (Working / Serving Notice / Immediate Joiner)

Have you worked with EPC companies before? If yes, please mention company names.

📩 Send your updated CV to: anjali.mishra@parkconsultants.in

